A report following an investigation into the death of Enock Mpianzi was released on Wednesday, revealing how a pattern of negligent decisions led to his death on a school camp. JOHANNESBURG - Following the death of 13-year-old Parktown Boys' High School pupil Enock Mpianzi on a school camp in January, the Gauteng Department of Education instructed Harris Nupen Molebatsi Attorneys to conduct an investigation. The findings of the investigation were released on Wednesday, revealing how a pattern of negligent decisions led to his death. Read the executive summary of the report of the forensic investigation below:  Enock Mpianzi Death Executive Summary Report by Janice Healing on Scribd 